	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Mbombela – Two bodies were discovered near the N4 highway in Emalahleni, Mpumalanga, on Wednesday. Police spokesperson Brigadier Leonard Hlathi said a suspect had been arrested on charges of murder. ALSO READ: Body found burnt to ashes inside Mercedes-Benz in Limpopo "We discovered two bodies, but we cannot yet confirm their identities," Hlathi told News24. "We still have the bodies and we are still investigating. I will only be able to give confirmation once a post-mortem and DNA tests have been concluded." Two children were recently abducted from their home in Vosman, also in Emalahleni, in the early hours of January 28. ALSO READ: Husband arrested after body of policewoman found in Randfontein Officers launched a manhunt after three armed men broke into the home and abducted a 13-year-old girl and a one-year-old baby. Hlathi was unable to confirm whether there was a possible link between the two incidents.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  